  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is being done to see if the Nova Creatinine Meter can give a correct measure of
      creatinine (a blood test used to measure kidney function) when the blood is taken from a
      capillary (smallest type of blood vessels). The Nova Creatinine Meter is a hand held device
      that can be used in a clinic to measure creatinine in about 50 seconds. Current laboratory
      creatinine testing can take up to an hour. Since chemotherapy patients need to have their
      creatinine measured prior to treatment, this meter could make testing easier and faster.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
